profile_data.summary:
At Ahold Delhaize USA, I leverage advanced analytics to transform large datasets into strategic insights. With a Master's degree in Analytics specializing in Statistical Modeling from Northeastern University, my role encompasses building data analytics solutions to drive business growth, designing KPI-tracking reports and dashboards to measure performance, and performing complex data analysis to enhance customer satisfaction and retention.

I lead a cross-functional team and employ statistical modeling and data analysis tools including SQL, Python, and R, Power BI, Databricks, Alteryx, and Advanced Excel to communicate findings and drive data-informed decisions. I am also a certified Tableau Desktop Specialist. My expertise in data analysis and reporting as well as more than five years of professional experience help to deliver actionable intelligence, ensuring the organization's competitive edge in the dynamic retail landscape.
profile_data.headline: Senior Data Analyst | Master's in Analytics

experience.description:
•	Design and build reports and dashboards that track KPIs and metrics, provide insights and communicate findings to clients
•	Extract large data sets from Azure Data Lake and perform data analysis on millions of sales transactions (using SQL, Python, R, Alteryx, Databricks, and Power BI) to identify customer trends, measure sales and campaign performance, customer engagement, and channel engagement to increase customer satisfaction and retention
•       Collaborate with cross-functional partners to identify business needs, complete data analysis, deliver effective presentations of findings and recommendations to management
•      Collaborate with predictive analytics team and third-party vendor to develop customer behavioral models that track customer engagement and customer segmentation, guide audience development, support marketing campaign and sales goals
•	Lead a cross functional group (Data Science, Campaign Management, Finance, and Operations Planning) to provide corporate level metrics reporting for the senior leadership team
•	Collaborate with business stakeholders to develop corporate level metrics to evaluate customer engagement, channel engagement, and financial impact
•	Conduct post-campaign and test/control analysis, measure sales performance and impact (e.g., incremental lift and ROI), provide actionable insights to clients, communicate findings, and make recommendations for audience selections and offer targeting
•	Manage projects to deliver advanced analytical solutions and apply agile development methodologies
•	Guide interns on data analysis and building reports
experience.title: Senior Data Analyst, Advanced Analytics

experience.description:
•	Perform data collection, data mining, data cleaning, and data wrangling.
•	Conduct data analysis and build models in R and Python for decision making
•	Deliver quantitative results and create data visualization to identify trends and insights.
